UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Jose JIMENEZ-PALACIOS, also known as Jose Jimenez-Palacio, Defendant-Appellant. No. 08-40182

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Aug. 18, 2009. James Lee Turner, Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Southern District of Texas, Houston, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. J. Alberto Alarcon, Hall, Quintanilla & Alarcon, Laredo, TX, for Defendant-Appellant. Before HIGGINBOTHAM, DAVIS, and CLEMENT, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM: *

The attorney appointed to represent Jose Jimenez-Palacios has moved for leave *315to withdraw and has filed a brief in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Jimenez-Palacios has not filed a response. Our independent review of the record and counsel’s brief discloses no nonfrivolous issue for appeal. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be *315published and is nol precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
